==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[impulsio]]''.

===Noun===
'''impulsion'''

# The act of [[impel]]ling or driving [[onward]], or the state of being [[impelled]]; the sudden or momentary [[agency]] of a [[body]] in [[motion]] on another body; also, the impelling force, or impulse.
# [[influence|Influence]] acting [[unexpectedly]] or [[temporarily]] on the [[mind]]; sudden [[motive]] or [[influence]]; [[impulse]].

